# Monstera-fed Project Conventions

Monstera-fed is a self-hosted ActivityPub / Mastodon-compatible server written in Go 1.26.

## Key docs

- `docs/SPEC.md` — project specification
- `docs/ERROR_HANDLING.md` — sentinel errors, wrapping, HTTP mapping
- `docs/TESTING.md` — testify, golangci-lint, test conventions
- `docs/NATS_CONVENTIONS.md` — stream names, subject patterns
- `docs/IMPLEMENTATION_ORDER.md` — build sequence and validation milestones
- `docs/ADR/` — detailed design documents per subsystem (01–10)

## Architecture rules

- `internal/domain` has zero internal imports — pure types and sentinel errors.
- `internal/service` never imports `internal/api`. Dependencies point inward toward `domain`.
- No layer below `internal/api` imports `net/http` or references HTTP status codes.
- Errors use `fmt.Errorf("context: %w", err)` wrapping. HTTP mapping is handler-only via `api.HandleError`.
- IDs are ULIDs via `internal/uid`.
- Config is 12-factor (env vars only) via `internal/config`.

## Code style

- Use `require` for preconditions, `assert` for verifications in tests.
- Use `t.Helper()` in all test helpers.
- No comments that just narrate what the code does.
- Structured logging via `slog` — no `fmt.Printf` or `log.Println`.
